---
import CaseStudyLayout from "../layouts/CaseStudyLayout.astro";

const meta = [
  { label: "Year", value: "2020" },
  { label: "Client", value: "Toyota" },
];
---

<CaseStudyLayout
  pageTitle="Toyota - Sammy Norris"
  meta={meta}
  description="A web-based car configurator for Toyota, giving users the tools to spec their perfect vehicle from engine to interior. I owned the design execution across more than 70% of the screens."
  signoff="Designed at Brandwidth"
  signoffYear="2020"
>
  <Fragment slot="title">Toyota</Fragment>

  <!-- Figure 01 -->
  <figure class="figure is-loose is-bind-top" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-1-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-1.jpg" alt="Toyota configurator hero" loading="eager" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter I - Challenge -->
  <section class="chapter is-tight" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">I.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The challenge</h2>
    </header>

    <blockquote class="chapter__quote">
      Give people a tangible sense of ownership before they ever stepped into
      a dealership.
    </blockquote>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        Toyota needed a configurator that let users custom-build their car online - walking through engine specs, colour options, and luxury interior details - and make it feel real enough to drive them into a dealership.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 02 -->
  <figure class="figure is-loose" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-2-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-2.jpg" alt="Configurator build stages" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter II - Process -->
  <section class="chapter is-tight" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">II.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The process</h2>
    </header>

    <h3 class="chapter__h2">
      Prototype, recolour, <em>test, repeat.</em>
    </h3>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        Working from initial direction set by the lead designer, I led the majority of screen design across the build flow. I designed and produced colour-accurate vehicle asset variants across Toyota's full range in Photoshop - every configuration had to feel authentic, not approximate. I prototyped interaction patterns for the build flow and ran wide-scale A/B tests on layout variants to validate decisions with real user behaviour.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 03 -->
  <figure class="figure is-loose-max" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-3-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-3.jpg" alt="Recoloured Toyota assets" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Chapter III - Outcome -->
  <section class="chapter" data-reveal>
    <header class="chapter__head">
      <span class="chapter__num" aria-hidden="true">III.</span>
      <h2 class="chapter__label b2">The outcome</h2>
    </header>

    <h3 class="chapter__h2">
      A formative one. <em>Shipped live.</em>
    </h3>

    <div class="chapter__body">
      <p class="b1">
        The configurator shipped live. It was an early-career project and a formative one - working at the pace and precision a brand like Toyota demands, on something production-ready with real user traffic.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Figure 04 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-4-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-4.jpg" alt="Toyota configurator detail" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>

  <!-- Figure 05 -->
  <figure class="figure" data-reveal>
    <picture>
      <source media="(max-width: 768px)" srcset="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-5-m.jpg" width="2250" height="3000" />
      <img src="/images/projects/toyota/image-toyota-5.jpg" alt="Toyota configurator screens" loading="lazy" width="2400" height="1800" />
    </picture>
  </figure>
</CaseStudyLayout>
